artifacttype_d118451c-0816-3aa5-8b89-311.name: Customer Behavior insights flow
artifacttype_d118451c-0816-3aa5-8b89-311.description: An electronics company wants to analyze consumer behavior by using analytics and cognitive technology. The company wants to understand consumer behavior and sentiments so that it can predict churn, cross-sell, and upsell opportunities. A business analyst submits data sets for analytical processing after bringing multiple data sets together using a cognitive platform. The cognitive platform helps extract deep insights from a large volume of internal and external structured and unstructured data sources. The system enriches the corpus with entities, concepts, relationships, sentiment, and emotion so that advanced text analytics can be performed on the unified data set. In this solution, the cognitive platform helps bring together a wide ranging data set and a structured representation of key information from the data sets for the analytical engine to execute supervised and unsupervised learning techniques.

artifacttype_d118451c-0816-3aa5-8b89-311.name: Data collection runtime flow
artifacttype_d118451c-0816-3aa5-8b89-311.description: An organization wants to provide their knowledge workers with easier access to deeper insights from data and to capture signals faster for better decision making. Creating a new text analytics pipeline can take months, slowed down by engineering and integration problems. A discovery service leverages cognitive functions to uncover entities, concepts, relationships, sentiment, emotion, and taxonomy, thus enriching the data. Knowledge workers can now interact with the system, leveraging the new cognitive insight instead of using traditional exact keyword match on content. The solution federates structured and unstructured data from internal sources, external content sources, and hosted curated content. The results can be further enhanced with custom annotations using machine learning and rules-based approaches, which can provide highly relevant and contextual results

coreInfo.description:
Some of the significant challenges that are unique to the cognitive discovery architecture implementation include:
*   Decision makers want to extract deeper insight from content and capture signals faster for better decision making. For example, customer support teams can discover hidden insights on customer pain points, behaviors, and needs to improve agent productivity.
*   Organizations want to reduce the complexity of gathering and preparing information. For example, field service teams can federate information from manuals, FAQ documents, and collaboration sites to locate hard-to-find answers.
*   Firms want to bring new and innovative solutions to market faster. For example, a research group can build rapid prototypes with multiple data sources to syndicate reports with deeper insights, experimenting with different facets of the information.
Get deeper insights from structured and unstructured content beyond what is obvious by enriching content with cognitive functions such as sentiment.

coreInfo.description:
Gain insights to inform decisions

The IBM WatsonÂ® Discovery service adds a cognitive engine to your application to search content and apply analytics to it. With that information, you can identify patterns and trends and gain insights that drive better decision-making.

Imagine having all of the data that you need to answer questions. The Watson Discovery service can process data from various sources, including MicrosoftÂ® Word, PDF, HTML, and JSON documents. Processing occurs in several ways:

  • With APIs, you can upload content by using an application or create a custom upload mechanism.
  • With discovery tooling, you can upload locally accessible files for configuration and testing.
  • With Data Crawler, you can upload of a large number of files from a supported repository, such as an IBMÂ® DB2Â® database, by using the command line.
Both publicly available data and your enterprise-specific data are processed and then enriched to be used by your application. Data enrichment provides a collection of text analysis functions that derive semantic information from your content. You can provide text, HTML, or a public URL and use natural language-processing techniques to get a high-level understanding of your content and obtain detailed insights, such as directional sentiment from entity to object. Enrichment extracts entities, relationships, keywords, sentiments, and more.

After the data is processed and enriched, itâ€™s securely stored and available to only your application. In addition to the private enterprise data that you include for use by your application, you can tap into pre-enriched data sets that are publicly available, such as the Discovery News collection. Discovery News includes primarily English-language news sources that are updated continuously, with over 300,000 new articles and blogs added daily from more than 100,000 sources.

The Watson Discovery service provides search capabilities through queries. The search engine finds matching documents from the processed data. Then, the engine applies a formula that provides relevance scoring to return the best answer to the query. When an application uses the Watson Discovery service, the people who use that application can gain insight from textual data. These examples are typical:

  • Customer service applications that support a workflow to find and deliver the answers to complex customer questions

  • Social media and news channel applications that provide real-time visibility to perceptions about products, services, and brands, and then correlate todayâ€™s results with historical results

  • Research applications that extract consolidated industry and domain-specific insights from vast numbers of research and other documents.

Provide insights by using a powerful cognitive engine

Businesses that build applications by using Watson Discovery benefit in several ways:

  • Deliver applications that integrate the natural language processing (NLP), search, analytics, and machine learning capabilities from the Discovery service.
  • Use APIs or tools to make your data, third-party data, and public data available for use in your application.
  • Keep your data secure and private.
  • Use a powerful cognitive engine to comb through vast amounts of data to provide answers to questions, detect trends and patterns, and provide insights that are surfaced through your application.

To learn more about building such applications, see the Discovery reference architecture.

Cognitive discovery concepts

To better understand Watson Discovery concepts, consider this example:

Millions of people fly every day. As travelers prepare for their flights, questions frequently arise about everything from what they can bring on the plane to rules about security procedures. To improve customer service, an airline can develop an application by using the Watson Discovery service to answer customers' questions.

To develop an air-travel concierge application, the cognitive team identifies the types of questions that the application must be able to address. Then, the data scientist works with the knowledge engineer to collect the data that can be used to answer the questions.

An air-travel concierge application likely needs to include any FAA rules that apply to customer travel. An airline might also have airline-specific rules and guidelines. The data team uses APIs and tools to process and enrich the data for the application. In parallel, application developers develop a web app that customers can use to ask their questions and receive responses.

When the application is ready, the airline customers can ask questions, which are sent via the application logic to the Watson Discovery service. The service processes the queries and returns results to customers through the web app.

For additional resources on this architecture, see - https://www.ibm.com/cloud/architecture/architectures/cognitiveDiscoveryDomain

coreInfo.description: An organization wants to provide their knowledge workers with easier access to deeper insights from data and to capture signals faster for better decision making. Creating a new text analytics pipeline can take months, slowed down by engineering and integration problems. A discovery service leverages cognitive functions to uncover entities, concepts, relationships, sentiment, emotion, and taxonomy, thus enriching the data. Knowledge workers can now interact with the system, leveraging the new cognitive insight instead of using traditional exact keyword match on content. The solution federates structured and unstructured data from internal sources, external content sources, and hosted curated content. The results can be further enhanced with custom annotations using machine learning and rules-based approaches, which can provide highly relevant and contextual results
coreInfo.label: Data collection runtime flow

coreInfo.description: External content can be ingested through a custom application using ingestion APIs.

In the back end, internal content is ingested from various enterprise content repositories via the Watson Discovery Service Data Crawler, Watson Discovery Service tooling, or a custom application using ingestion APIs.

coreInfo.description: An organization wants to provide their knowledge workers with easier access to deeper insights from data and to capture signals faster for better decision making. Creating a new text analytics pipeline can take months, slowed down by engineering and integration problems. A discovery service leverages cognitive functions to uncover entities, concepts, relationships, sentiment, emotion, and taxonomy, thus enriching the data. Knowledge workers can now interact with the system, leveraging the new cognitive insight instead of using traditional exact keyword match on content. The solution federates structured and unstructured data from internal sources, external content sources, and hosted curated content. The results can be further enhanced with custom annotations using machine learning and rules-based approaches, which can provide highly relevant and contextual results
coreInfo.label: End User Runtime Flow

coreInfo.description: User enters a search query through the web application using business concepts of the domain.
IBM Watson Discovery Service processes the query and returns the results to the discovery application.
A custom developed discovery application orchestrates all of the business flow and internal API calls to the discovery service.

Connectivity from the enterprise network to the cloud is secured through VPN and edge services, which consists of domain name server, CDN server, firewall, and load balancers. This group of services handles the request and gets it to the right destination securely.

coreInfo.description: An electronics company wants to analyze consumer behavior by using analytics and cognitive technology. The company wants to understand consumer behavior and sentiments so that it can predict churn, cross-sell, and upsell opportunities. A business analyst submits data sets for analytical processing after bringing multiple data sets together using a cognitive platform. The cognitive platform helps extract deep insights from a large volume of internal and external structured and unstructured data sources. The system enriches the corpus with entities, concepts, relationships, sentiment, and emotion so that advanced text analytics can be performed on the unified data set. In this solution, the cognitive platform helps bring together a wide ranging data set and a structured representation of key information from the data sets for the analytical engine to execute supervised and unsupervised learning techniques.
coreInfo.label: Customer Behavior insights flow

coreInfo.description: The discovery application invokes the analytical model.

The user in an electronics company logs in to the custom built cognitive search and discovery platform that is powered by Watson Discovery Services. The user clicks the menu item to generate a list of customers with high propensity to churn. Alternatively, the user can click the menu to generate a list of customers and potential cross-sell and upsell opportunities for the sales campaign teams to use.
Optionally, Watson Knowledge Studio can be used to impart the domain awareness to the natural language understanding service.
The results of the analytical models are persisted in the data store and returned to the business analyst.
An ingestion application based on IBM Watson Discovery Service ingests information from the public data sources.
The discovery application accesses the content federated within the Watson Discovery Service and returns the result of query to the discovery application.

Custom annotators and dictionaries created using Watson Knowledge Studio bring domain-specific content into the repository. This content is annotated using both rules-based and machine learning-based techniques to enrich the data.
